This is a "Lock" demo for the feature FSM (Finite State Machine) of Akka.

See: http://cntt.tv/nodes/show/559

To run:

1. Install JVM, Git, and SBT
2. Checkout Akka to ~/plain/akka and compile
   cd ~/plain
   git clone http://github.com/jboner/akka.git
   cd akka
   sbt update
   sbt dist
3. Checkout the demo and open SBT's console
   cd /tmp
   git clone http://github.com/ngocdaothanh/lock-fsm-akka.git
   cd lock-fsm-akka
   sbt console
4. From the console, run
   import se.scalablesolutions.akka.actor.Actor
   import demo.{Lock, Button}
   val l = Actor.actorOf(new Lock("2010"))
   l.start
   l ! Button('2')
   l ! Button('0')
   l ! Button('1')
   l ! Button('0')
   l.stop
   exit
